event-driven, non-blocking I/O model 


 npm install --save socket.io


To start a node server
1. node <path to the server js file>

Things to know abt require:
(http://stackoverflow.com/questions/9901082/what-is-this-javascript-require)
1. require() is built into Node.js to load modules 
2. require returns a value, depending on what the module exposes using exports or module.exports

